Description: Replace `jiter.from_json` with `pydantic_core.from_json`
 The streaming chat completions helper imports `from_json` from jiter
 at module load time, so the bare presence of the import is enough to
 break `import openai` on a host that lacks jiter. jiter is a Rust
 JSON accelerator that Noble does not package; pydantic_core (already
 in the Avalan PPA) exposes the same `from_json` API and is a
 perfectly adequate substitute for the OpenAI streaming-parse path.
 Debian sid's python-openai ships the same substitution in its own
 packaging; this is the Avalan-overlay equivalent.
Author: Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-21

--- a/src/openai/lib/streaming/chat/_completions.py
+++ b/src/openai/lib/streaming/chat/_completions.py
@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@
 from typing import TYPE_CHECKING, Any, Generic, Callable, Iterable, Awaitable, AsyncIterator, cast
 from typing_extensions import Self, Iterator, assert_never

-from jiter import from_json
+from pydantic_core import from_json

 from ._types import ParsedChoiceSnapshot, ParsedChatCompletionSnapshot, ParsedChatCompletionMessageSnapshot
 from ._events import (
